history.content:
If autonomous lunar rovers, microgravity experiments, high altitude balloons, and designing/launching satellites sound like projects you want to make part of your Berkeley experience, come join us at the Space Technologies at California (STAC) Spring 2022 info sessions!

 

Info Sessions:

Wednesday, 1/26 from 7-8 pm

Thursday, 2/3 from 7-8 pm

 

STAC is a student space program that strives to push the space industry incrementally further. Our 60+ members come from all majors and backgrounds and collaborate on several innovative research projects throughout the year. Come meet our members, hear about what we're working on, and learn how you can make an impact in the space industry!

 

We have a very chill application process which will be due 2/4 at 11:59 PM. 

Application and zoom links: linktr.ee/calstac 

 

Questions?: execs@stac.berkeley.edu
